<font color="#FF0000">PRAYER</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 13  9:19:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
CET wants to know if anything else (besides praying) has calmed my scars.  The answer is &quot;Yes&quot;.  Thinking a lot about why we went in the first place, why I went in the first place, recognizing that the people involved were trying their best, finding a wonderful lady and settling down and having a family (as of this writing, complete with a dog) getting out in the wilderness and studying wild critters, recognizing the natural beauty that was and is available everywhere in the world.  All that gives me peace.  Does Jesus (or Mohammed, or whoever) have anything to do with that?  I don't know, and on one level I really don't care.  On another level, I recognize the value of sprituality, but I don't see it as taking the form of &quot;praying to Jesus&quot; in any simplistic sense.
